FBIS3-21710 "jptdd010__l94015" JPRS-TDD-94-010L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 7 March 1994 LATIN AMERICA BOLIVIA Laboratory Destroyed, Several Colombian Traffickers Arrested in Santa Cruz PY0203030994 La Paz Television Nacional Network in Spanish 0100 GMT 2 Mar 94 PY0203030994 La Paz Television Nacional Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] It has been reported in Santa Cruz that the Special Antinarcotics Force has arrested more than 35 drug traffickers, most of them Colombians who operated in the outskirts of San Jose de Chiquitos. The forces destroyed a laboratory that processed 450 kg of cocaine per week, and seized weapons including M-16 automatic rifles, shotguns, revolvers, and rifles. They are also confiscated automobiles and houses owned by the drug traffickers in the city of Santa Cruz. It has also been reported that from 20 to 30 top Colombian drug traffickers linked to the Medellin and Cali cartels could be operating in Bolivia. They enter or leave Bolivia time after time as tourists going across the border with Brazil.
